mkdir ~/lab9_osint && cd ~/lab9_osint
Create a Google Dork operators reference file:

nano google_dorks_reference.txt
Add this content:

GOOGLE DORK OPERATORS
=====================

Basic Operators:
- site:domain.com          Search within specific domain
- filetype:pdf             Find specific file types
- intitle:"keyword"        Search in page titles
- inurl:"keyword"          Search in URLs
- intext:"keyword"         Search in page content
- cache:url                View cached version
- related:domain.com       Find related websites

Advanced Operators:
- "exact phrase"           Exact phrase matching
- keyword1 OR keyword2     Either term
- keyword1 AND keyword2    Both terms
- -keyword                 Exclude term
- *                        Wildcard
- 2020..2023              Range operator

Security-Focused Examples:
- intitle:"index of"       Directory listings
- filetype:sql "password"  SQL files with passwords
- inurl:admin              Admin panels
- intitle:"login"          Login pages
Save and exit (Ctrl+X, Y, Enter).

